to the editor re seat of government seat of the pants by diane cole weekend section feb 9 it is a shame that ms cole and her son had a less than perfect experience during their visit to the united states capitol such a visit should be a reminder that our democracy is the greatest the world has ever seen to that end congress has allocated 100 million as the first step in creating a public private partnership to expand the capitol the campaign for democracy 's front door will match the appropriation with private money the visitor center will house food and rest facilities and an exhibit space for interactive educational stations art and document exhibits and a permanent display of statues and art in addition two 250 seat auditoriums will show short films that will make each visitor appreciate the experience vic fazio bob michel washington feb 12 2001 the writers former members of congress are on the board of the fund for the capitol visitor center

